definitions.definition: ( fishing ) Gear consisting of a long and thick mainline , with baited hooks attached at intervals by means of branch lines called snoods or gangions .
( firefighting ) A long cable used to raise or lower loads from a helicopter when landing is not possible.

main_definition: ( fishing ) Gear consisting of a long and thick mainline , with baited hooks attached at intervals by means of branch lines called snoods or gangions .

definitions.definition: A slackline which runs a considerable distance
